
    IT WAS a sad day for the families of 11 crash victims and the community of Hazyview, Mpumalanga who gathered to bid farewell to loved ones on Saturday.All the speakers described the incident as heartbreaking.Speaking on behalf of the families, Calvin Mhlanga said: “We appreciate the support we’ve received. In such times, people come together to help each other. We believe our brothers and sisters are at peace, wherever they are. Goodbyes are never easy.”The accident happened on the R538 between Hazyview and White River when the taxi they were travelling in crashed into three cows on their way to church.The victims, Dinah Mathebula, Rose Makhubela, Joyce Cubayi, Matricia Mawelele, Thando Dibakoane, Sarah Nkuna, Beauty Mgwenya, Precious Ngwenya, Prudence Mnisi, Antonio Matsinhe and Joyce Mkhabela were all laid to rest on Saturday. One victim was buried in Mozambique.if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjstwaX87xljq9FfQ-fp5K-wPNzFmnQFqeLBMZTJxSr-3I1HYE2C8XL7aANhgqUalJBKnlniiWAay2RoTbk73KSK551J_26FqKCCkT-Ng7GMeKmRCKHLVLrsXzQYot9a2mcoqvfz2y5VhCOyIgEPKEUVA4r7o9-c9DtB1A4OmOLwWop3Uh0ltq5cihkFDIjx3o6ZI_30UZWjx3LcT_m0cH_WZGXlDFqCYvOvHnT9JFQ4VZu7PE6u9kUolgsrkooiYnyRc_fYzfnvUH4c4iZZRmL5PAdXX1iQ\x26sig\x3dCg0ArKJSzAHslkkrPeUyEAE\x26urlfix\x3d1\x26adurl\x3d")

   
